image.altText: Steve Smith raises his bat

items.synopsis: Steve Smith and Travis Head have already put on 251 runs, and they'll look to press home Australia's advantage over India on day two of the World Test Championship final at The Oval. Follow all the updates in our live blog.

title.children: Steve Smith reaches his century on day two of WTC final

liveBlogPostPrepared.plaintext: Oh that's a shame for Travis Head, just a handful of runs shy of his best Test score. He tried to hook, got a bit of glove on it and it was easy pickings for Bharat behind the stumps. It's a good ball from Siraj, who is cockahoop and screaming in delight, as is Kohli, who has found that trampoline that he was on for much of the first two sessions yesterday. It's a terrific innings through from Head. He's out for 163 from 174 balls.
liveBlogPostPrepared.title: GOT HIM! TRAVIS HEAD HAS TO GO!

children.content: Oh that's a shame for Travis Head, just a handful of runs shy of his best Test score.
He tried to hook, got a bit of glove on it and it was easy pickings for Bharat behind the stumps.
It's a good ball from Siraj, who is cockahoop and screaming in delight, as is Kohli, who has found that trampoline that he was on for much of the first two sessions yesterday.
It's a terrific innings through from Head.

liveBlogPostPrepared.plaintext: 152 off 164 balls for Travis Head. He has gone past 150 four times in Test cricket, Head. That's a decent conversion rate from century to BIG century. He gets off strike next ball. Smith defends one, and then gets a single off his pads. Then Head is rapped on the pads and, although the ball was going a long way down leg, that's still a slight positive for and Indian team that look bereft of any idea on how to take wickets.
liveBlogPostPrepared.title: 150 for Travis Head!

liveBlogPostPrepared.plaintext: Doesn't get any easier than that, Smith gets there with another four, half volley onto his pads and he clips it away through midwicket. Mohammed Siraj has just copped an earful from his skipper for bowling that dross onto Smith's pads. And rightfully so. Smith has 103 off 229 balls. His 31st Test century, his third at The Oval. What a player.
liveBlogPostPrepared.title: Century for Steve Smith!
